column2: WHAT ARE THE PROCEDURES FOR RESIDENCY IN JORDAN
column5: Upon coming to Jordan#Comma the student is granted a temporary residence permit for a period of one month#Comma #Newline        so that the student can register and enroll in the university in which he wishes to study#Comma #Newline        and after completing the registration procedures and during the period of the temporary residence permit mentioned above#Comma#Newline        the student must visit the nearest security center (police) to determine his place of residence#Comma #Newline        and then the student must prepare the required documents#Comma which are#Newline         Passport#Comma student proof from the Admission and Registration Unit#Comma #Newline         old residence card in case of residence renewal#Comma #Newline         exit and re-entry visa for students who hold a travel document#Comma #Newline         and submit it to the International Students Division at#Newline         the Deanship of Student Affairs at the Hashemite University to start the procedures for obtaining annual residency.

column2: WHAT IS THE COST OF LIVING IN JORDAN
